{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"unsetenv","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"variable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar"},{"text":">!)","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that on some systems, when variables are overwritten, the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"memory used for the previous variables and its value isn’t reclaimed."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You should be mindful of the fact that environment variable handling"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in UNIX is not thread-safe, and your program may crash if one thread","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"calls ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_unsetenv()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" while another thread is calling "},{"code":"getenv()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". (And note"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that many functions, such as ","type":"text"},{"code":"gettext()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"getenv()"},{"type":"text","text":" internally.) This"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"function is only safe to use at the very start of your program, before"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"creating any other threads (or creating objects that create worker","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"threads of their own)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need to set up the environment for a child process, you can","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"use ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_get_environ()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to get an environment array, modify that with"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_environ_setenv()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"g_environ_unsetenv()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and then pass that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"array directly to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"execvpe()"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_spawn_async()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", or the like.","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/unsetenv(variable:)"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/unsetenv(variable:)"]}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"func","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib8unsetenv8variableySPys4Int8VGSg_tF","title":"unsetenv(variable:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"unsetenv","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"variable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar"},{"text":">!)","kind":"text"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Function"},"abstract":[{"text":"Removes an environment variable from the environment.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/unsetenv(variable:)":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","title":"unsetenv(variable:)","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/unsetenv(variable:)","abstract":[{"text":"Removes an environment variable from the environment.","type":"text"}],"fragment